1. Building vim from source: 
    https://github.com/ycm-core/YouCompleteMe/wiki/Building-Vim-from-source
    The YCM requires the vim version up to 8.2 
2. Install the vundle to manage the vim packages. 
    https://github.com/VundleVim/Vundle.vim#quick-start
2. Installing the YCM: 
    If using the vundle to manage the vim packages modify the .vimrc syntax 
    comment the ```set rtp+=~/.vim/bundle/vundle``` and comment out the ```set rtp+=~/.vim/bundle/Vundle.vim```. 
    https://github.com/ycm-core/YouCompleteMe#installation 
